    "The reconstructions were normalized and converted from 16-bit to 8-bit images.",
    "To save memory and computational time, small volumes of interest were selected from the wrist and the ankle (wrist = 6.3 × 6 × 3.7 cm, ankle = 6.6 × 6.3 × 4.8 cm).",
    "For the knee scan, the full joint was processed (10 × 10 × 10 cm, output size = 1884 × 1932 × 1988 voxels) on the Puhti supercomputer (https:// resea rch. csc.",
